💔💕 Watching your last baby grow up is like witnessing the closing of a beautiful chapter in your life. It’s a reminder that time waits for no one, and childhood is fleeting. The days of endless cuddles, bedtime stories, and playful giggles are slowly fading away, making room for a new phase of life.

Yet, amidst the bittersweet emotions, I am filled with immense pride. I see the incredible little people they are becoming, with their own dreams, passions, and unique personality. It’s a testament to the love, guidance, and support we have provided throughout the years. And that fills my heart with an overwhelming sense of joy.

So, to all the parents out there who understand this bittersweet journey, let’s cherish every moment. Let’s hold our babies a little tighter, savor their innocence a little longer, and create memories that will last a lifetime. Because even though it’s hard to let go, we can find solace in knowing that we have given them the foundation to soar high and chase their dreams.

To my last baby, as you grow up, remember that my love for you knows no bounds. You will always be my little one, no matter how big you become. Embrace the world with open arms, but never forget the love and warmth that surrounds you. And know that I will always be here, cheering you on, every step of the way.

Let’s talk about something that can truly brighten up your day and strengthen your relationship - the importance of greeting your spouse at the door! 😍

We all lead busy lives, and sometimes it’s easy to get caught up in the hustle and bustle. But taking just a few moments to greet your partner with a warm smile and a loving embrace can make a world of difference! Here’s why:

🫶🏽It sets the tone for the rest of the day: Imagine coming home after a long day, feeling tired and stressed. But as soon as you open that door, your amazing spouse is there, ready to welcome you with open arms. Suddenly, all the worries melt away, and you’re reminded of the love and support waiting for you. It instantly uplifts your mood and creates a positive atmosphere for the evening ahead!

So, let’s make it a habit to greet our partners at the door with love and enthusiasm! Let’s create a home filled with warmth, appreciation, and connection. 💜

Doing our best to model to our children that they can run to God in every situation, we start our day off with morning prayers before Drew leaves for work. Since our kids are still young, prayer time is short and chaotic, but that’s okay. I grew up doing daily family prayers, and I deeply cherish those times.

Here are a few reasons why praying big and often can help our children understand the significance of running to God rather than relying on the world:

1. Demonstrating trust in God: When we pray big prayers, we show our children that we trust in God’s power and ability to intervene in our lives. This trust can inspire them to develop their own faith and seek God’s help in times of need.

2. Building resilience and faith: Praying big prayers helps our children understand that God is capable of working miracles and answering even the most challenging requests. This builds their faith and resilience, teaching them to turn to God when faced with difficult situations instead of relying solely on worldly solutions.

3. Shaping their worldview: Consistent prayer helps shape our children’s worldview, reminding them that God is the ultimate source of truth, love, and guidance. This understanding can help them navigate the complexities of the world with a solid foundation rooted in God’s principles.

I encourage you to try praying big and loud prayers in front your babies!! 🫶🏽

Most people don’t know…

I was never the kid that dreamt of having a family. As a young girl, I was all in on my dance and acting career. Then in college, I was focused on getting into medical school. But God had other plans for me. I get to be a mom and a wife to these precious humans. I can confidently say that God’s plan is always better.

The simple moments of life lately…

Watching our children achieve milestones is incredible, like the first steps or a heartfelt “I love you.” But what really sticks with me are the simple, everyday moments. It’s the bedtime talks, shared jokes, and cozy cuddles that make motherhood special. While the big milestones are like landmarks, it’s these little moments that create the true magic of our journey together. They’re the heartwarming notes in our family melody, forming a sweet and unforgettable song of motherhood.

Within the embrace of our family, I strive to create a haven of warmth and safety for my kids. Each moment becomes a stitch, weaving a comforting narrative that defines their childhood. Yet, in the honest fabric of our journey, I acknowledge it’s not always perfect. There are struggles, and I stumble at times. But through it all, I remain committed to being the unwavering presence that makes their growing years a sanctuary of love and security.
